item.title: I Don't Want to Live on the Moon, Harmonica Tab
VarietiesofBoredom.md
item.description: At least, there are two types of boredom. Type I Boredom: You are picking rosemary off of sprigs. Filling out piles of paperwork. Doing homework that is too easy for you. You are tired of what it is you are doing. You would very much rather be doing something else–anything else. Type II Boredom: You have nothing to do, and you’re not exactly sure what to do. The experiental equivalent of when you’re hungry, but there’s nothing in the fridge that you want to eat.
